den%20visa'%20to%20lure%20millionaires%20back.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EBritain%20is%20facing%20an%20exodus%20of%20super%20wealthy%20residents%20amid%20changes%20to%20its%20tax%20regime.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20country%20is%20seen%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Bhostile%26quot%3B%20environment%20for%20the%20world's%20richest%20people%2C%20one%20analyst%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20UK%20is%20reportedly%20considering%20reviving%20its%20%26quot%3Bgolden%20visa%26quot%3B%20plan%20to%20attract%20wealthy%20foreign%20investors%20as%20it%20faces%20the%20prospect%20of%20a%20record-breaking%20outflow%20of%20millionaires.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20proposed%20investor%20visa%2C%20which%20Bloomberg%20reported%20is%20under%20discussion%20by%20senior%20government%20ministers%2C%20would%20target%20high-net-worth%20individuals%20(HNWI)%20willing%20to%20invest%20in%20strategically%20important%20sectors%20such%20as%20artificial%20intelligence%2C%20clean%20energy%2C%20and%20biotech.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20UK%20Home%20Office%20declined%20to%20comment%20on%20any%20potential%20plans.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20move%20comes%20amid%20growing%20concerns%20that%20the%20UK's%20crackdown%20on%20tax%20perks%20for%20the%20wealthy%20%E2%80%94%20including%20the%20abolition%20of%20the%20non-dom%20regime%20in%20April%20%E2%80%94%20could%20drive%20a%20mass%20departure%20of%20wealthy%20residents%20and%20their%20capital.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20April%20analysis%20by%20the%20Centre%20for%20Economics%20and%20Business%20Research%20found%20that%20if%20half%20of%20former%20non-domiciled%20taxpayers%20left%20the%20country%2C%20the%20Treasury%20could%20face%20net%20losses%20of%20%C2%A32.4%20billion%20(%243.26%20billion)%20in%20the%20first%20year%20alone.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUntil%20its%20repeal%2C%20the%20%26quot%3Bnon-dom%26quot%3B%20regime%20had%20allowed%20wealthy%20foreign%20nationals%20living%20in%20the%20UK%20to%20avoid%20paying%20UK%20tax%20on%20income%20earned%20abroad%2C%20making%20Britain%20especially%20attractive%20to%20global%20elites%20with%20international%20assets.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20according%20to%20Henley%20%26amp%3B%20Partners'%20Private%20Wealth%20Migration%20Report%202025%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frich-used-to-flock-to-the-uk-now-theyre-fleeing-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EBritain%20is%20projected%20to%20lose%2016%2C500%20millionaires%20this%20year%20alone%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20more%20than%20any%20other%20country%20on%20record%2C%20including%20China%2C%20in%20part%20due%20to%20tax%20changes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20a%20dramatic%20reversal%20for%20a%20nation%20once%20seen%20as%20a%20hub%20for%20global%20wealth.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22London's%C2%A0financial%C2%A0district.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F686e5c42f748d8c055f53afb%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222667%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ELondon's%20status%20as%20a%20global%20base%20for%20the%20world's%20richest%20people%20is%20under%20threat.%3Cp%3ESteve%20Taylor%20%2F%20SOPA%20Images%2FSipa%20USA%20via%20Reuters%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22e435b92c-9087-48c5-a0aa-ccdbbe26e3c7%5C%22%3E'Much%20of%20the%20damage%20has%20already%20been%20done'%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAnalysts%20blamed%20rising%20taxes%2C%20political%20instability%2C%20and%20the%20end%20of%20the%20non-dom%20status%20for%20the%20departure%20of%20the%20ultrawealthy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20no%20doubt%20a%20refreshed%20golden%20visa%20scheme%20could%20help%20slow%20the%20exodus%20and%20potentially%20lure%20some%20HNWIs%20back%20%E2%80%94%20but%20let's%20be%20clear%3A%20much%20of%20the%20damage%20has%20already%20been%20done%2C%26quot%3B%20Nigel%20Green%2C%20CEO%20of%20global%20financial%20advisory%20giant%20deVere%20Group%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20UK's%20competitiveness%20in%20the%20global%20race%20for%20wealth%20has%20taken%20a%20significant%20hit%20in%20recent%20times%2C%20and%20trust%20doesn't%20return%20overnight%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BStill%2C%20for%20those%20with%20long-standing%20business%2C%20personal%2C%20or%20cultural%20ties%20to%20Britain%2C%20it%20could%20be%20enough%20to%20start%20a%20conversation%20again.%20It's%20not%20a%20silver%20bullet%2C%20but%20it%20may%20be%20worth%20a%20shot.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Bank%20of%20England%20and%C2%A0London's%C2%A0financial%C2%A0district.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F686e5d0a3d5881a51c1cf2f0%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223670%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20City%20of%20London%20has%20been%20a%20financial%20hub%20for%20hundreds%20of%20years.%3Cp%3EThomas%20Krych%20%2F%20SOPA%20Images%2FSipa%20USA%20via%20Reuters%20Connect%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EMatthew%20Lesh%2C%20UK%20country%20manager%20at%20consultancy%20Freshwater%20Strategy%2C%20blamed%20what%20he%20called%20%26quot%3Bthe%20toxic%20mix%20of%20historically%20high%20taxes%20and%20the%20abolition%20of%20the%20non-dom%20regime.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20it%20has%20%26quot%3Bresulted%20in%20thousands%20of%20the%20world's%20wealthiest%20individuals%20fleeing%26quot%3B%20the%20UK%2C%20adding%3A%20%26quot%3BIt's%20often%20forgotten%20that%20not%20only%20do%20the%20wealthiest%20have%20the%20widest%20shoulders%2C%20but%20also%20the%20longest%20legs.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20UK's%20National%20Audit%20Office%2C%20wealthy%20individuals%20paid%20%C2%A3119%20billion%20(%24161%20billion)%20in%20personal%20taxes%20in%202023-24%2C%20accounting%20for%2025%25%20of%20all%20UK%20personal%20tax%20receipts.%20The%20top%2029%2C000%20earners%20alone%20were%20responsible%20for%20%C2%A334%20billion%20in%20income%20tax.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BA%20new%20'golden%20visa'%20could%20be%20an%20attractive%20prospect%20for%20some%20of%20the%20world's%20wealthiest%2C%26quot%3B%20Lesh%20continued%2C%20%26quot%3Bbut%20if%20they%20arrive%20to%20find%20themselves%20paying%20exorbitant%20taxes%20for%20poor%20public%20services%20and%20threatened%20by%20a%20new%20'wealth%20tax%2C'%20they%20are%20unlikely%20to%20stick%20around%20for%20long.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%225a9dd2ae-8466-4446-9841-7c86217604fe%5C%22%3EA%20tarnished%20history%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20UK's%20original%20Tier%201%20investor%20visa%2C%20introduced%20in%202008%2C%20granted%20residency%20to%20foreigners%20who%20invested%20at%20least%20%C2%A31%20million%20(%241.35%20million).%20That%20threshold%20was%20raised%20to%20%C2%A32%20million%20in%202014.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20route%20was%20scrapped%20in%20February%202022%20amid%20mounting%20concerns%20over%20illicit%20finance%20and%20national%20security%2C%20especially%20after%20Russia's%20invasion%20of%20Ukraine.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%202023%20government%20review%20found%20that%20a%20minority%20of%20golden%20visa%20holders%20before%202015%20were%20flagged%20as%20high%20risk%2C%20with%20some%20holders%20possibly%20linked%20to%20corruption%20or%20organized%20crime.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20history%20has%20left%20a%20bitter%20legacy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20letter%20to%20Chancellor%20Rachel%20Reeves%20this%20month%2C%20a%20coalition%20of%20anti-corruption%20groups%20warned%20that%20a%20new%20investor%20visa%20would%20%26quot%3Bexpose%20the%20UK%20to%20acute%20national%20security%20risks%20by%20facilitating%20foreign%20influence%20and%20the%20flow%20of%20illicit%20finance.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2242cd96f1-d1b4-47cb-9312-f3b512b4fc19%5C%22%3E'Change%20the%20narrative'%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESupporters%20argue%20that%20a%20new%20plan%20could%20be%20more%20tightly%20designed%2C%20and%20is%20urgently%20needed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJames%20Quarmby%2C%20head%20of%20private%20wealth%20at%20law%20firm%20Stephenson%20Harwood%2C%20told%20BI%20the%20government%20%26quot%3Bcan't%20afford%20to%20ignore%20the%20reality.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20you've%20got%20a%20lot%20of%20people%20leaving%2C%20you've%20got%20two%20choices%20%E2%80%94%20either%20stop%20them%20by%20changing%20the%20rules%20that%20are%20driving%20them%20out%2C%20or%20attract%20new%20people%20in.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAn%20investment%20visa%20could%20change%20the%20narrative%20in%20the%20UK%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BRight%20now%2C%20the%20perception%20among%20wealth%20holders%20and%20their%20advisors%20is%20that%20the%20UK%20has%20become%20a%20hostile%20place%20for%20capital.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EQuarmby%20said%20the%20visa%20should%20be%20bold%20and%20transparent%2C%20with%20meaningful%20incentives%3A%20%26quot%3B%C2%A32%20million%20is%20too%20low.%20I'd%20recommend%20a%20%C2%A34%20to%20%C2%A35%20million%20minimum%20investment.%20But%20that%20must%20come%20with%20tax%20incentives.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20government%20also%20needs%20to%20guarantee%20policy%20stability%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%20%26quot%3BPeople%20aren't%20going%20to%20relocate%20their%20lives%20and%20businesses%20to%20the%20UK%20only%20to%20have%20the%20rules%20change%20again%20in%20two%20years.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGreen%20echoed%20that%20view%3A%20%26quot%3BThe%20number%20one%20deterrent%20is%20uncertainty.%20Tax%20policy%20has%20become%20unpredictable%2C%20and%20for%20HNWIs%2C%20that's%20a%20dealbreaker.%20It's%20not%20just%20about%20rates%20%E2%80%94%20it's%20about%20tone%2C%20messaging%2C%20and%20direction%20of%20travel.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%222b0f01f8-4996-4a1f-a4dd-f6f7ee63df97%5C%22%3EA%20political%20balancing%20act%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20proposal%20puts%20the%20UK%20government%20in%20a%20tricky%20position.%20While%20the%20government%20faces%20intense%20fiscal%20pressure%20and%20limited%20room%20for%20big%20tax%20hikes%2C%20it%20must%20also%20appease%20a%20parliamentary%20base%20wary%20of%20any%20measures%20seen%20as%20overtly%20pro-wealth.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%227273%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Rachel%20Reeves%2C%20UK%20chancellor%20of%20the%20exchequer%2C%20walks%20down%20Downing%20Street%20in%20London%20on%20July%209%2C%202025.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F686e5da2f748d8c055f53b16%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224851%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ERachel%20Reeves%2C%20UK%20Chancellor%20of%20the%20Exchequer%2C%20faces%20a%20difficult%20balancing%20act.%3Cp%3EDan%20Kitwood%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EQuarmby%20predicts%20Labour%20will%20%26quot%3Bquietly%26quot%3B%20pursue%20an%20investor%20visa%20under%20a%20different%20label.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20doubt%20they'll%20call%20it%20a%20golden%20visa%20%E2%80%94%20it'll%20be%20something%20more%20palatable%2C%20like%20a%20'Global%20Talent%20Visa'%20with%20an%20investment%20component.%20That%20way%2C%20it%20sounds%20more%20blue-collar.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20he%20sees%20the%20odds%20of%20action%20as%20high.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20at%20least%20a%2060-40%20chance%20this%20happens.%20The%20Treasury%20is%20running%20out%20of%20options.%20If%20you're%20out%20of%20blood%20to%20squeeze%20from%20the%20current%20tax%20base%2C%20you%20need%20new%20blood.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20Green%20cautioned%3A%20%26quot%3BThe%20UK%20used%20to%20be%20a%20magnet%20for%20global%20wealth%20%E2%80%94%20now%20it's%20often%20seen%20as%20a%20cautionary%20tale.%20Rebuilding%20trust%20will%20require%20sustained%20effort%20and%20meaningful%20reforms%2C%20not%20just%20a%20visa%20tweak.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fuk-losing-crown-as-global-hub-for-the-worlds-rich-2025-7%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1753264746000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F686